cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for modeling spatiotemporal trajectories over long time horizons using expert demonstrations. This involves reasoning about both long-term and short-term goals, which is achieved through a hierarchical policy class instantiated as a hierarchical neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves modeling trajectories in sports, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
